summary:
The Committee's mandate applies to measures imposed in previous resolutions and will hold regular consultations with concerned Member States.

The Panel of Experts' mandate is extended until 29 February 2016, and its tasks include:
- Assisting the Committee in carrying out its mandate (a);
- Gathering information on implementation of measures and incidents of non-compliance (b);
- Providing a midterm update by 30 July 2015 and a final report by 31 December 2015 (c);
- Submitting progress updates to the Committee (d);
- Assisting in refining and updating information on designated individuals and entities (e);
- Providing information on potential designees (f).

The Panel is called upon to cooperate with other Panels or Groups of Experts and devote attention to analysis of illicit trafficking networks.

The document also urges cooperation from the CAR, neighbouring States, and Member States to combat regional criminal networks and armed groups involved in illegal exploitation and smuggling of natural resources.

All parties, Member States, and UN bodies are urged to ensure cooperation with the Panel of Experts and unhindered access to execute its mandate. 

The Special Representatives of the Secretary-General for Children and Armed Conflict and Sexual Violence in Conflict are requested to share relevant information with the Committee.

All States are called upon to report to the Committee on actions taken to implement the imposed measures.
